What do you want to challenge us with next?

Shoutout to @oppo and @eyecannndy for the inspiration.

Tutorial:
1. Before shooting

choose clothing that contrasts well with the background because you need to magic mask/auto mask/rotobrush.
2. Put your camera on a tripod and shoot yourself walking in a zig zag position towards the camera. Make sure each spot you walk to is closer to the camera than the previous spot.
3. In your editor

speed ramp or cut your clips so there is ~6 frames of you walking from spot to spot.
4. Magic mask yourself from the background. Your mask does NOT need to be perfect because when you blur

the edges disappear. Feather the mask edge with a blur and erode/contract so it isn't so pixelated. Export or precomp the mask with alpha and then reimport.
5. Layer your timeline with the sped up clip on bottom and echos above then cut the echo clips so they appear when you want them to. Once done cutting

freeze frame each echo.
6. Add directional blur to all your moving echos. The blur should be in the direction you are walking. Play around with blur strength - the same setting on a far and close echo will have dramatically different results.
7.Put your first masked clip on top of all the echos and you're golden.

Tips to make it look even better:
- freeze frame the shadows at your feet so your echos aren't floating in space - do this with a simple feathered polygon
- keyframe the strength of the blur to increase every time you walk past an echo (for example

we increased strength of blur on the echos from window to desk).
